<span id="freeTextContainer11071102888924827473">A polemic parable about the evils wreaked on Kenya by colonialism and capitalism, written in Thiong&apos;o’s native tongue and smuggled out of prison on sheets of toilet paper. A fascinating back story but it is doggedly didactic, and even agreeing with all the major points I still can’t imagine many readers actually enjoying the work itself. </span>
  <span id="freeText11071102888924827473" style="display:none">A polemic parable about the evils wreaked on Kenya by colonialism and capitalism, written in Thiong'o’s native tongue and smuggled out of prison on sheets of toilet paper. A fascinating back story but it is doggedly didactic, and even agreeing with all the major points I still can’t imagine many readers actually enjoying the work itself. </span>
