        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3468926970" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13400746039101838400">Having read other works by Thiong&apos;o, I was a bit disappointed in this one. I loved the opening/beginning but I lost interest as the novel progresses. I get the novel is political and is being straightforward and archetypical to achieve its purpose, but I was left wanting more of the character development that I know Thiong&apos;o does very well. When the fleshed out Wariinga starts becoming a symbol more than a &quot;living&quot; character, I was left a bit disappointed. I know this book is important and the f</span>
  <span id="freeText13400746039101838400" style="display:none">Having read other works by Thiong'o, I was a bit disappointed in this one. I loved the opening/beginning but I lost interest as the novel progresses. I get the novel is political and is being straightforward and archetypical to achieve its purpose, but I was left wanting more of the character development that I know Thiong'o does very well. When the fleshed out Wariinga starts becoming a symbol more than a "living" character, I was left a bit disappointed. I know this book is important and the fact that it was written on toilet paper in prison speaks to its power, and it is a crucial book in terms of post-colonialism, but I was left wanting a bit more. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13400746039101838400" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

