        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2180415797" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3023976534640206815">A hard, good read in these times for many reasons, not least of which being the realization, like Wariinga&apos;s of &quot;the larger societal malaise and that much of the misfortune stems from the Western, capitalist influences,&quot; as the book jacket puts it. <br/><br/>&quot;For unto the man of property more will be given, but from the poor man will be taken even the little that he has kept in reserve.&quot;<br/><br/>&quot;Anything who knows anything about modern theft knows very well that it is these financial institutions that govern ever</span>
  <span id="freeText3023976534640206815" style="display:none">A hard, good read in these times for many reasons, not least of which being the realization, like Wariinga's of "the larger societal malaise and that much of the misfortune stems from the Western, capitalist influences," as the book jacket puts it. <br /><br />"For unto the man of property more will be given, but from the poor man will be taken even the little that he has kept in reserve."<br /><br />"Anything who knows anything about modern theft knows very well that it is these financial institutions that govern everything today. ... Money is the heart that beats to keep the Western world on the move."<br /><br />"... the churches, the schools, the poetry, the songs, the cinema, the beer halls, the clubs, the newspapers will all act as brain-washing poisons ..." <br /><br />A morality tale, perhaps, but is anyone listening?</span>
  <a data-text-id="3023976534640206815" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

